      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Grapes of Ire</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Jeffrey Heller letter on plan to translate Harry Potter books from 'English' to 'American' for United States readers comments on possible irritating results (July 10 Peter H Gleick Op-Ed)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Harry Potter, Minus a Certain Flavour,'' by Peter H. Gleick (Op-Ed, July 10), about the decision by the publisher of the American edition to translate the books from ''English'' into ''American'': American literature is sometimes edited to suit the British market. The most irritating example I've seen is a British edition of ''The Grapes of Wrath'' in which Ma Joad refers to a ''gallon a petrol.''</p>
        <p>JEFFREY HELLER  Cranford, N.J., July 11, 2000</p>
      </block>
